# Initialize an empty list to collect reformatted data
data = []

# Initialize variables to hold the current year and metrics
current_year = None
metrics = {}

# Iterate through the dataframe rows
for _, row in analysis_df.iterrows():
    if pd.notna(row[0]):  # Detect year
        if current_year is not None:  # Save the previous year's metrics before resetting
            data.append([current_year] + list(metrics.values()))
        current_year = row[0]
        metrics = {}
    else:  # Collect metrics
        metric_name = row.index[0]
        metric_value = row[1]
        metrics[metric_name] = metric_value

# Append the last collected year's data
if current_year is not None:
    data.append([current_year] + list(metrics.values()))

columns = ['Year', 'Total Comp', 'Base as % of Total Comp', 'Base as % of Total Sales',
           'Base as % of GM', '$ Sales/ $ Base', '$ GM / $ Base']

# Create a new dataframe with the structured data
reformatted_df = pd.DataFrame(data, columns=columns)
